import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Legal Assistance | Eligibility"
  description="Learn about the legal assistance available to UK veterans applying for the Armed Forces Compensation Scheme. Understand your rights and get support for your claim.">
  <div class="container my-5">
    <h1 class="display-4 mb-4">Legal Assistance for AFCS Claims</h1>
    <div class="row g-4">
      <div class="col-lg-8">
        <p class="lead">Navigating the Armed Forces Compensation Scheme (AFCS) can be complex. This page outlines the legal assistance available to help you understand your rights and support your claim process.</p>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Types of Legal Assistance</h2>
        <p>Various forms of legal support are available:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Initial claim advice</li>
          <li>Representation during appeals</li>
          <li>Guidance on complex cases</li>
          <li>Support for judicial reviews</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Free Legal Advice Services</h2>
        <p>Several organisations offer free legal advice to veterans:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Veterans Legal Support Network</li>
          <li>Armed Forces Legal Action helpline</li>
          <li>Local Citizens Advice Bureaus</li>
          <li>Pro bono services from law firms specialising in military law</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">When to Seek Legal Assistance</h2>
        <p>Consider seeking legal help if:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Your claim has been rejected and you want to appeal</li>
          <li>You're unsure about your eligibility</li>
          <li>Your case involves complex medical or service history</li>
          <li>You're considering a judicial review</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Choosing a Legal Representative</h2>
        <p>When selecting legal assistance, consider:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Experience with AFCS claims</li>
          <li>Understanding of military service and related injuries</li>
          <li>Success rate in similar cases</li>
          <li>Clear fee structure (if applicable)</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Preparing for Legal Consultation</h2>
        <p>To make the most of legal assistance:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Gather all relevant documents (medical records, service history, etc.)</li>
          <li>Write down a clear timeline of events</li>
          <li>Prepare a list of questions</li>
          <li>Be honest and thorough in your discussions</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-4">
        <div class="card bg-light mb-4">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3 class="h5">Related Information</h3>
            <ul class="list-unstyled">
              <li><a href="/eligibility/appeal-process" class="text-decoration-none">Appeal Process</a></li>
              <li><a href="/policy/legislation" class="text-decoration-none">AFCS Legislation</a></li>
              <li><a href="/support/claim-advice" class="text-decoration-none">Claim Advice</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card mb-4">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3 class="h5">Legal Assistance Helpline</h3>
            <p>For immediate legal advice on your AFCS claim, contact our helpline.</p>
            <p class="fw-bold">0800 XXX XXXX</p>
            <a href="/legal-support" class="btn btn-primary">Learn More</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
